Pre Calculus MA 123 MA 124   Calculus   Analytic Geometry I   II MA 125 MA 126   Quantitative Methods I   II MA 215   Multivariable Calculus MA 220   Probability   Statistics for Engineers   Scientists MA 311   Differential Equations Location 700 Level of Preston Library  Open Math Lab  OML  No appointments necessary  The OML 2016 Spring semester regular hours of operation are  Daytime 1200 1600  Monday  Thursday Evening 1800 2300  Sunday  Thursday     At the Mathematics Education and Resource Center  our mission is to  support our Cadet Corps in their pursuit of mathematical studies  engage our VMI faculty and staff in their goals of maintaining rigor and excellence in their respective disciplines  and work with our community in their desire for productive  inspired  and healthy citizens    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 